Georeference

How to use make the Georeference
1. Download the Lucene 3.4
2. Create a new Java project in Eclipse
3. Put the GeoIndexWriter.java, Georeference.java, and GeoreferenceTest.java in the package
4. Add these jar files to the project's path
	- lucene-core-3.4.0.jar
	- lucene-misc-3.4.0.jar
	- lucene-queries.3.4.0.jar
	- lucene-spatial.3.4.0.jar
5. Run the GeoreferenceTest.java as a test

How to run the Georeference Java servlet
1. Download the Tomcat Server
2. Create a Dynamic Web Project
3. Put the GeoIndexWriter.java, Georeference.java, and GeoreferenceServlet.java in the package
4. Copy these jar files to the directory WebContent/WEB-INF/lib
	- lucene-core-3.4.0.jar
	- lucene-misc-3.4.0.jar
	- lucene-queries.3.4.0.jar
	- lucene-spatial.3.4.0.jar
5. Add these jar files to the project's path
6. Put web.xml in WebContent/WEB-INF
7. In web.xml init params, pecify the locations of your data files and locations you want index files to be stored in
8. Run the GeoreferenceServlet.java on the Tomcat server
9. Run the WebClientTest.java as a test
